## Output Format

Provide 10 titles in a clean table format:

| # | Emotion | Chars | Mobile | Keywords | Title |
|---|---------|-------|--------|----------|-------|
| 1 | CURIOSITY | 47 | ✓ | AI, coding, demo | "Title here..." |
| 2 | DESIRE | 52 | ✗ | tutorial, build, fast | "Title here..." |
| 3 | FEAR | 45 | ✓ | warning, mistake, avoid | "Title here..." |

**Column Details:**
- **Emotion**: CURIOSITY, DESIRE, or FEAR
- **Chars**: Exact character count of the title
- **Mobile**: ✓ if under 50 chars (mobile-safe), ✗ if 50+ chars
- **Keywords**: 2-4 primary keywords from the title (comma-separated)
- **Title**: The complete YouTube title in quotes

## Expected Output

A markdown table with 10 title options that:
- Trigger at least one emotion (Curiosity/Desire/Fear)
- Are 40-50 characters when possible (mobile-optimized)
- Front-load important keywords
- Use power words strategically
- Accurately reflect video content
- Include 2-4 relevant keywords per title
- Are ready to use on YouTube
